=== main.rs ===
// Phenotype tooling CLI facade — `pt <subcmd>` entrypoint.
//
// This binary is intentionally a thin wrapper around `phenotype_cli::run()` so
// that the entire behaviour is unit-testable from `lib.rs` without spawning a
// subprocess. Keeping `main` minimal is the standard pattern for CLI design.

use std::process::ExitCode;

fn main() -> ExitCode {
    // Delegate all behaviour to the library entry point so that integration
    // tests can exercise the same code path via `phenotype_cli::run`.
    match phenotype_cli::run() {
        Ok(()) => ExitCode::SUCCESS,
        Err(err) => {
            // Print errors to stderr in a stable format so that downstream
            // tooling (CI logs, wrappers) can grep for `error:` reliably.
            eprintln!("error: {err}");
            // Use a non-zero exit code that the error can hint at via Debug
            // (we deliberately avoid Display-with-newlines to keep parsing
            // stable for scripting).
            ExitCode::FAILURE
        }
    }
}

=== lib.rs (first 50 lines) ===
1://! phenotype-cli: top-level CLI facade for the phenotype-tooling ecosystem.
2://!
3://! Provides a unified `pt <subcmd>` entry-point that dispatches to the absorbed
4://! sub-crates (`docs-health`, `quality-gate`, `fr-trace`, `release-cut`,
5://! `sbom-gen`, etc.) via the spine's subcommand router pattern.
6://!
7://! ## Design
8://!
9://! - **Subcommand enum**: each absorbed crate declares a variant with its
10://!   own clap-derived arg set. New crates add a variant without touching
11://!   the router.
12://! - **Versioning**: `--version` reports the workspace `Cargo.toml`
13://!   version (single source of truth).
14://! - **Error handling**: any subcommand failure is converted to a
15://!   `ClapError` and the process exits non-zero with a user-facing
16://!   message (no panics in `main`).
17://!
18://! See SPEC.md §CLI for the full contract.
19:
20:use clap::{Parser, Subcommand};
21:
22:/// CLI version string — sourced from the workspace `Cargo.toml`.
23:pub const VERSION: &str = env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION");
24:
25:/// CLI name (short alias).
26:pub const NAME: &str = "pt";
27:
28:/// Top-level CLI args.
29:#[derive(Debug, Parser)]
30:#[command(
31:    name = NAME,
32:    version = VERSION,
33:    about = "Phenotype tooling — unified CLI for absorbed sub-crates",
34:    long_about = "pt is the unified entry-point for the phenotype-tooling ecosystem. \
35:                  It dispatches to docs-health, quality-gate, fr-trace, release-cut, \
36:                  sbom-gen, and other absorbed sub-crates via subcommands."
37:)]
38:pub struct Cli {
39:    /// Subcommand to execute.
40:    #[command(subcommand)]
41:    pub command: Command,
42:
43:    /// Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv).
44:    #[arg(short, long, action = clap::ArgAction::Count, global = true)]
45:    pub verbose: u8,
46:}
47:
48:/// All supported subcommands.
